================================================================================
2. COMMERCIAL LICENSE
================================================================================

A Commercial License is granted upon purchase of a valid license key
(format: DARIO-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-SUF) from the Copyright Holder. The scope
of the Commercial License (tier, parallel workers, vertical squads, term)
is determined by the tier suffix and is defined in the file
`orchestrator/license_manager.py` (TIERS dictionary, lines 130-630).

Commercial License grants the Licensee:

  (a) The right to use the Software in production on the machines
      authorized by their tier's `max_parallel` value;
  (b) The right to receive software updates published to the same
      repository for the duration of their paid subscription;
  (c) Email support at the response level specified in their tier.

